minisign
------------------------------------------
Minisign is a dead simple tool to sign files and verify signatures.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.5-1
  libsodium23-1.0.18-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://jedisct1.github.io/minisign/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jedisct1/minisign/archive/0.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack minisign-0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./minisign-0.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/minisign-0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/minisign-0.9-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(minisign)
  /usr/bin/minisign.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/minisign.README
  /usr/share/doc/minisign/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/minisign/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/minisign.1.gz

